Interface ListMap<K,V extends Identifiable<K>>

public interface ListMap<K,V extends Identifiable<K>>
extends List<V>

This class brings the best of both, List and Map. So you can simply iterate, like you would do with any List or get a item by his list position. You can also search for an value by searching for his key (id), like you would do with any Map implementation ( #getById(Identifiable))

Author:
Hannes Dorfmann

Method Detail

getById

V getById(K id)
Get the value by the key. The access will be as fast as accessing a Map. If there are more elements with the same key in the list, than the first one (with the lowest index) will be returned.

Parameters:
id - The values id.
Returns:

removeById

V removeById(K id)
Remove all items in the list that matches have this key. More formally, removes all elements with the index i such that (o==null ? get(i)==null : o.equals(get(i))) (if such an element exists)

Parameters:
id -
Returns:
The first element that has been found to be removed or null, if there is no such element
